description:
Indonesian President Prabowo Subianto on Sunday (Aug 31) announced in a live national address that parliament will revoke controversial perks for MPs that have sparked days of protests and rioting.

Flanked by party leaders, including PDI-P chair Megawati Soekarnoputri, Mr Prabowo said party leaders have taken firm action against their MPs, and that sanctions will take effect from Monday.

He said the right to peaceful assembly must be protected, but warned that violence, including looting and destruction of facilities, would not be tolerated.

Read more: https://cna.asia/4lODUxh
